# AgriEdge-Detect: Real-Time Foreign Object Detection for Agricultural Machinery

## Complete Implementation Blueprint

> **Purpose of this document:** This is a fully self-contained specification for building a production-quality prototype that demonstrates embedded AI for predictive sensor systems in agriculture. Any developer or LLM reading this document should be able to build the entire project from scratch, file by file, with zero ambiguity.

---

## 1. PROJECT OVERVIEW

### 1.1 What We Are Building

A complete end-to-end prototype called **"AgriEdge-Detect"** that simulates a foreign object detection system for a forage harvester. When a rock, metal piece, or other foreign object enters the crop flow, the system detects it in real-time from vibration/acoustic sensor data and triggers a blade-brake warning.

### 1.2 Why This Exists

This prototype accompanies an application to the **European Summer of Code 2026** project: *"Embedded AI for Predictive Sensor Systems in Agriculture 4.0"*, sponsored by a major European agricultural machinery manufacturer. The actual project uses proprietary datasets with 1000+ real-world foreign object events recorded at millisecond granularity from vibration, acoustic, and mechanical sensors.

Since the proprietary dataset is not available pre-selection, this prototype uses **publicly available industrial vibration/time-series datasets** to demonstrate the exact same pipeline the real project would use.

### 1.3 What the Prototype Demonstrates

| Capability | How We Demonstrate It |
|---|---|
| Foreign object event detection | Binary classification on time series windows |
| Feature extraction & preprocessing | Sliding window segmentation, normalization, optional feature engineering |
| sktime integration | All models built using `sktime` estimators (both classic ML and deep learning) |
| Performance metrics (TPR, FPR, detection time) | Full evaluation pipeline with confusion matrices, ROC curves, advance detection time |
| Embedded/edge readiness | PyTorch → ONNX export + INT8 quantization with benchmarked latency |
| Explainability | Temporal importance curves showing which part of the signal triggered detection |
| Real-time visualization | Live-scrolling dashboard simulating harvester sensor feed with instant alerts |

### 1.4 Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| ML Framework | `sktime` (time series), [torch](file:///p:/sktime/sktime/regression/deep_learning/base/_base_torch.py#446-476) (deep learning backend) |
| Data | FordA dataset (built into sktime) + synthetic agricultural vibration data |
| Model Export | ONNX Runtime, PyTorch quantization |
| Dashboard | Python + Streamlit (for the live real-time visualization) |
| Visualization | Plotly (interactive charts), Matplotlib (static reports) |
| Language | Python 3.10+ |

